@UndeadBlow You might find this script useful:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/tools/ci_build/windows/libtensorflow_cpu.sh
As pointed out by @gunan, the .so file built is actually a .dll file on Windows, you'll have to rename it to .dll to make it work on Windows.

